Operation System setup instructions...
1. Download and Run Debian from Microsoft Store on Windows OS
2. using apt install... curl, xz-utils, git, direnv, and wget
3. install nix via curl

First time VSCode setup...
1. Open it from Windows
2. Set Debian to be default terminal
3. Navigate to project directory on WSL
4. Run ```code -r .``` in the home directory, and you will be prompted to install VSCode Server via wget

Maintaining dependencies...
1. Be aware of all apt package versions that were installed
2. Be aware of all other packages installed outside of apt
  * code-server via wget
  * nix via curl
3. Be aware of all nix packages

Git setup...
Don't know if I want to have individual repos per project, or one large project repo.

Setup remote on Windows...
1. navigate to Desktop/home/remotes
2. git init --bare <project-type>/<project-name>.git
Setup working directory on WSL...
3. go to the working directory on WSL
4. git init
5. git remote add winrepo /mnt/c/Users/kenru/Desktop/home/remotes/<project-type>/<project-name>.git
6. save and commit and push progress
Setup a working directory on Windows...
7. clone a working copy into a similar windows directory: /Desktop/home/projects/<project-type>/<project-name>.git

Workflow...
1. Open VSCode from Windows
2. View entire WSL home from code note: find way to toggle hidden files/folders
3. Find and work on project!

Ruby with Nix...
1. Use the nix built versions of ruby from nixpkgs-ruby
2. Use bundix to read Gemfile.lock and generate gemset.nix

Installing Gems...
1. gem install gem-name
2. bundle install